docs.abstract: Some are reconsidering the rules surrounding protests and demonstrations on and off the field.
docs.snippet: Some are reconsidering the rules surrounding protests and demonstrations on and off the field.
docs.lead_paragraph: After Colin Kaepernick and other athletes caused a stir in 2016 by kneeling for the national anthem to protest racism and police brutality, leagues scrambled to set policies on such demonstrations. Now, in the wake of the killing of George Floyd and the nationwide protests it inspired, the issue may well arise again as American sports return. And some leagues are revisiting their rules.

headline.main: How Sports Leagues Regulate Athletes’ Activism
headline.print_headline: The Rules on Activism They Are A-Changin’

docs.abstract: As thousands of protesters took to the streets over the past week, artists, both amateur and professional, created a vast collection of drawings, paintings and illustrations in support of the protests and the Black Lives Matter movement.
docs.snippet: As thousands of protesters took to the streets over the past week, artists, both amateur and professional, created a vast collection of drawings, paintings and illustrations in support of the protests and the Black Lives Matter movement.
docs.lead_paragraph: Thousands of people have taken to the streets over the last week to protest police brutality and systemic racism, sparking a movement that has inspired hundreds of demonstrations across the country and ushered in a new wave of themed art.

headline.main: ‘The World is on Fire:’ Artists Respond to the Protests

docs.abstract: “We shouldn’t be screaming, ‘Trans Lives Matter,’ but we have to,” said Leiomy Maldonado, a ballroom icon. “We’re strong and we’re here to fight.”
docs.snippet: “We shouldn’t be screaming, ‘Trans Lives Matter,’ but we have to,” said Leiomy Maldonado, a ballroom icon. “We’re strong and we’re here to fight.”
docs.lead_paragraph: Earlier this year, videos emerged of members of the ballroom community voguing in hazmat suits, holding “kiki” battles via TikTok and creating hand washing tutorials with new coronavirus-inspired beats and chants. Then came the videos of members cat walking with protesters, dropping into “dips” in front of police cars, voguing at impromptu protest balls and marching the asphalt runway while holding Black Lives Matter signs.

docs.abstract: And what else you need to know today.
docs.snippet: And what else you need to know today.
docs.lead_paragraph: For most white Americans, interactions with the police happen rarely, and they’re often respectful or even friendly. Many white people don’t know a single person who’s currently behind bars.

docs.abstract: Amid a backlash and an ad boycott, “Tucker Carlson Tonight” is still attracting big audiences, another sign of the nation’s political divide.
docs.snippet: Amid a backlash and an ad boycott, “Tucker Carlson Tonight” is still attracting big audiences, another sign of the nation’s political divide.
docs.lead_paragraph: In recent weeks, Tucker Carlson, the conservative Fox News host, has challenged the Black Lives Matter movement, dismissed demonstrators as “criminal mobs,” accused a Texas police chief of “sounding more like a therapist than a cop” and mocked a CNN children’s special about racism that featured Elmo, the “Sesame Street” puppet.

headline.main: Advertisers Are Fleeing Tucker Carlson. Fox News Viewers Have Stayed.
headline.print_headline: Ads May Flee Carlson, But Viewers Stay Put
